{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34bbb1c0-0f97-4ee9-b2da-9ec06b031da8","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100+\ndotnet build            # check for breaking changes\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking API or behavioral changes affecting your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c93e80e8-a4e2-440e-9953-07782e843c24","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the relevant files.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"0400:A6C81:6FC012:802642:6A0529FB"},"id":"5130e094-ca06-4cb8-b6c5-3afc8d77d62f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:51.462Z","parentId":"b6115397-6cfd-4cd7-b1b5-a9649d4f69c1"}
